1
00:01:03,985 --> 00:01:07,738
Once upon a time, long, long ago...

2
00:01:21,002 --> 00:01:24,797
Once upon a time, long, long ago...

3
00:01:24,880 --> 00:01:25,881
Come on!

4
00:01:37,685 --> 00:01:40,729
Once upon a time, long, long ago...

5
00:01:41,439 --> 00:01:45,939
one unlucky sailor
fell under an ancient wicked curse.

6
00:01:46,611 --> 00:01:48,988
<i>And thusly, he became known</i>

7
00:01:49,071 --> 00:01:51,364
<i>as the dreaded Flying Dutchman.</i>

8
00:01:53,367 --> 00:01:56,745
<i>Legend has it,
the only way to lift his curse</i>

9
00:01:56,829 --> 00:02:00,249
<i>is through the pure heart
of an innocent.</i>

10
00:02:00,875 --> 00:02:03,043
<i>Henceforth, the Flying Dutchman</i>

11
00:02:03,127 --> 00:02:07,506
<i>is doomed to wander the seas
in search of this magical soul.</i>

12
00:02:07,590 --> 00:02:11,677
<i>A precious youth
with an innocent mind.</i>

13
00:02:11,761 --> 00:02:13,637
<i>Will he find this soul?</i>

14
00:02:15,848 --> 00:02:19,351
<i>Does such a soul even exist?</i>

15
00:02:24,774 --> 00:02:28,652
<i>Who lives
in a pineapple under the sea?</i>

16
00:02:40,122 --> 00:02:44,622
Meow. Meow. Meow.

17
00:02:52,885 --> 00:02:54,720
<i>Good morning!</i>

18
00:02:54,804 --> 00:02:58,390
<i>This is Rocket Fuel Randy on BKNI 101,</i>

19
00:02:58,474 --> 00:03:01,685
<i>and I got the jet fuel
to get you rocking.</i>

20
00:03:01,769 --> 00:03:04,855
<i>Are you ready to get the day started?</i>

21
00:03:05,356 --> 00:03:06,565
<i>Chicka-chickahh</i>

22
00:03:06,649 --> 00:03:07,650
I'm ready.

23
00:03:20,329 --> 00:03:22,247
Wah! Wah! Ooh!

24
00:03:23,874 --> 00:03:26,251
<i>Big things are happening today.</i>

25
00:03:26,335 --> 00:03:29,129
Today's the day! I just know it.

26
00:03:29,213 --> 00:03:31,298
<i>Things feel different.</i>

27
00:03:31,382 --> 00:03:34,259
My whole life is about to change.

28
00:03:34,719 --> 00:03:35,720
Meow.

29
00:03:35,803 --> 00:03:37,679
I know I said that yesterday, Gary.

30
00:03:37,763 --> 00:03:39,890
- Meow.
- And the day before.

31
00:03:39,974 --> 00:03:42,393
- Meow.
- And a bunch of days before that.

32
00:03:42,476 --> 00:03:44,436
But today is different.

33
00:03:48,441 --> 00:03:50,484
<i>Big things in store.</i>

34
00:03:54,488 --> 00:03:56,072
Well, what's it say, Gary?

35
00:03:56,157 --> 00:03:58,367
- Meow.
- What? That can't be.

36
00:03:58,451 --> 00:04:00,578
- Meow.
- Gary, what's it really say?

37
00:04:00,661 --> 00:04:01,662
- Meow-ow.
- Gary!

38
00:04:10,963 --> 00:04:13,423
- Meow.
- Whoo!

39
00:04:13,507 --> 00:04:15,300
Do you know what this means?

40
00:04:15,384 --> 00:04:16,968
- Meow.
- For the last time,

41
00:04:17,052 --> 00:04:18,595
we are not rehoming you.

42
00:04:18,679 --> 00:04:19,680
No, this means

43
00:04:19,764 --> 00:04:22,892
- I'm exactly 36 clams high!
- Meow.

44
00:04:22,975 --> 00:04:25,185
I know it doesn't seem like much,
Gary,

45
00:04:25,269 --> 00:04:28,563
but that half a clam I grew
changes everything.

46
00:04:28,647 --> 00:04:31,149
- Meow.
- That's right, Gary-licious.

47
00:04:31,233 --> 00:04:34,402
Everyone's gonna look at me
in a brand new way.

48
00:04:38,157 --> 00:04:40,159
<i>Big guy
Big guy</i>

49
00:04:40,242 --> 00:04:42,035
<i>Big, big guy
Big guy</i>

50
00:04:42,119 --> 00:04:44,287
Because now... I'm a big guy.

51
00:04:44,371 --> 00:04:46,790
<i>SpongeBob Big Guy Pants okay</i>

52
00:04:46,874 --> 00:04:48,542
<i>Big things 'bout to happen today</i>

53
00:04:48,626 --> 00:04:50,878
<i>I woke up feeling a brand new way</i>

54
00:04:51,921 --> 00:04:52,922
Big guy!

55
00:04:53,005 --> 00:04:55,090
<i>SpongeBob Big Guy Pants okay</i>

56
00:04:55,174 --> 00:04:56,466
<i>Tight fit, square hips</i>

57
00:04:56,550 --> 00:04:58,677
<i>Doing a dance in my big guy pants</i>

58
00:04:59,637 --> 00:05:00,971
Big guy.

59
00:05:01,055 --> 00:05:03,057
<i>SpongeBob Big Guy Pants okay</i>

60
00:05:03,766 --> 00:05:04,767
Big guy.

61
00:05:05,559 --> 00:05:07,310
<i>Ain't a jellyfish, but I'm the catch</i>

62
00:05:07,394 --> 00:05:09,521
<i>Feel like that fish
so I'm puffing my chest</i>

63
00:05:09,605 --> 00:05:10,939
Big guy.

64
00:05:12,441 --> 00:05:14,151
Well, catch you later, Gare Bear.

65
00:05:14,235 --> 00:05:16,153
I'm off to do some important stuff

66
00:05:16,237 --> 00:05:19,365
that only big guys like me
are allowed to do.

67
00:05:19,448 --> 00:05:20,449
Uh...

68
00:05:21,700 --> 00:05:23,743
Whew. We're gonna need
a bigger doorway.

69
00:05:24,829 --> 00:05:25,830
Meow.

70
00:05:26,413 --> 00:05:29,791
Morning, Squidward!
Want to hear my big news?

71
00:05:29,875 --> 00:05:31,459
Oh, sure.

72
00:05:31,544 --> 00:05:33,963
Let me go mark some time
on my calendar.

73
00:05:34,046 --> 00:05:35,380
Hmph!

74
00:05:35,464 --> 00:05:37,257
Great! Let me know when!

75
00:05:40,970 --> 00:05:42,221
Good morning, Patrick!

76
00:05:42,304 --> 00:05:43,680
Good morning!

77
00:05:44,265 --> 00:05:45,307
Who are you?

78
00:05:46,183 --> 00:05:47,642
Patrick, it's me!

79
00:05:50,563 --> 00:05:53,566
Grandma? You're upside down!

80
00:05:53,649 --> 00:05:55,734
No, Patrick, it's me, SpongeBob.

81
00:05:55,818 --> 00:05:59,154
You can't be SpongeBob.
He's far more diminutive.

82
00:05:59,238 --> 00:06:01,156
- He's what?
- Of reduced stature.

83
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:02,783
- Come again?
- Vertically challenged.

84
00:06:02,867 --> 00:06:04,285
- Say what now?
- He's shorter.

85
00:06:04,368 --> 00:06:07,412
Patrick, I can't believe all I do
is grow half a barnacle overnight,

86
00:06:07,496 --> 00:06:08,997
and now I'm 36 clams tall,

87
00:06:09,081 --> 00:06:13,001
and you don't even recognize
your best friend!

88
00:06:13,085 --> 00:06:17,506
Did you say you're 36 clams tall?

89
00:06:17,590 --> 00:06:19,383
Yes!

90
00:06:22,177 --> 00:06:23,595
You're a big guy now!

91
00:06:23,679 --> 00:06:25,389
This guy's a big guy!

92
00:06:25,472 --> 00:06:27,307
- So big!
- Really big!

93
00:06:27,391 --> 00:06:29,184
- Big! Big! Big!
- Guy! Guy! Guy!

94
00:06:29,268 --> 00:06:31,395
- Big! Big! Big!
- Guy! Guy! Guy!

95
00:06:31,478 --> 00:06:33,021
- Big! Big! Big!
- Guy! Guy! Guy!

96
00:06:35,190 --> 00:06:37,483
Look out, everyone. Really big.

97
00:06:37,568 --> 00:06:38,694
Really guy.

98
00:06:38,777 --> 00:06:42,071
Hey, Sandy,
notice anything different about me?

99
00:06:42,156 --> 00:06:45,284
Howdy, SpongeBob.
Did you get a new pair of shoes?

100
00:06:47,494 --> 00:06:48,495
Ouch!

101
00:06:48,829 --> 00:06:49,830
Hi, Plankton!

102
00:06:49,914 --> 00:06:52,958
Watch where you're going,
you big dummy!

103
00:06:53,042 --> 00:06:55,002
Aw. Thanks for noticing.

104
00:06:55,085 --> 00:06:56,127
Wait, no! Ow!

105
00:06:56,211 --> 00:06:58,922
Patrick, I've never felt
so respected before.

106
00:06:59,006 --> 00:07:00,382
Get used to it, buddy.

107
00:07:00,466 --> 00:07:04,219
And do you know what the best part
of being a big guy is?

108
00:07:05,387 --> 00:07:07,764
- What is it, Patrick?
- No, I'm asking.

109
00:07:07,848 --> 00:07:09,724
It means I finally get to do

110
00:07:09,808 --> 00:07:12,936
what every little guy dreams of doing
when they grow up.

111
00:07:13,020 --> 00:07:15,022
You don't mean...

112
00:07:15,105 --> 00:07:16,397
That's right.

113
00:07:16,482 --> 00:07:20,982
Ride the big guy roller coaster
at Captain Booty Beard's Fun Park!

114
00:07:21,320 --> 00:07:22,362
- Whoo-hoo!
- Whoo-hoo!

115
00:07:22,446 --> 00:07:25,657
This calls for an extra-special
bubble blow.

116
00:07:32,456 --> 00:07:34,749
To Captain Booty Beard's!

117
00:07:34,833 --> 00:07:36,501
Whoo-hoo!

118
00:07:36,585 --> 00:07:38,169
- Gimme a "big!"
- Big!

119
00:07:38,253 --> 00:07:39,754
- Gimme a "guy!"
- Guy!

120
00:07:39,838 --> 00:07:42,423
- What does that spell?
- 36 clams high!

121
00:07:49,598 --> 00:07:51,141
Don't waste my time, squirt.

122
00:07:53,644 --> 00:07:55,979
Next!

123
00:07:58,107 --> 00:08:01,110
Ugh, you again.

124
00:08:02,903 --> 00:08:04,571
Congratulations.

125
00:08:05,280 --> 00:08:07,532
- Patrick?
- It's official.

126
00:08:10,953 --> 00:08:12,996
Don't make me call security.

127
00:08:13,080 --> 00:08:14,956
Whoo-hoo! Yay!

128
00:08:56,123 --> 00:08:58,375
Patrick?

129
00:09:00,335 --> 00:09:01,336
Wait a minute!

130
00:09:01,420 --> 00:09:02,671
Huh?

131
00:09:02,755 --> 00:09:05,340
What's the matter?
I thought you were a big guy.

132
00:09:05,424 --> 00:09:08,093
I am! I mean... I am.

133
00:09:08,177 --> 00:09:09,553
I just, uh, promised

134
00:09:09,636 --> 00:09:11,971
someone else that I'd ride with them,
that's all.

135
00:09:12,056 --> 00:09:14,308
Oh, yeah? Who?

136
00:09:14,391 --> 00:09:16,226
The guy who--

137
00:09:16,310 --> 00:09:18,395
Um, I--

138
00:09:19,438 --> 00:09:20,689
Mr. Krabs!

139
00:09:20,773 --> 00:09:22,399
Oh. That makes sense.

140
00:09:22,483 --> 00:09:24,651
- Phew.
- Let's go get him!

141
00:09:28,906 --> 00:09:29,907
Sorry!

142
00:09:29,990 --> 00:09:31,408
Coming through!

143
00:09:35,120 --> 00:09:36,621
Heads up, Mr. Krabs!

144
00:09:36,705 --> 00:09:40,375
It's time to ride the Shipwreck!
Whoo-hoo!

145
00:09:40,459 --> 00:09:42,586
What are ya talking about, Patrick?

146
00:09:42,669 --> 00:09:46,047
The roller coaster!
Get your head in the game.

147
00:09:46,131 --> 00:09:49,134
Remember that big
terrifying roller coaster?

148
00:09:49,218 --> 00:09:52,429
- Nope.
- We had a deal to ride it together.

149
00:09:52,513 --> 00:09:54,806
- Nope.
- So I couldn't ride it

150
00:09:54,890 --> 00:09:59,019
if you were too busy
to ride it with me. Hmm?

151
00:09:59,686 --> 00:10:00,853
Wha--

152
00:10:03,690 --> 00:10:04,774
Hoo-whoo-whoo-whoo!

153
00:10:07,027 --> 00:10:08,695
Shipwreck!

154
00:10:08,779 --> 00:10:10,071
Hmm.

155
00:10:10,155 --> 00:10:11,406
Hmm.

156
00:10:12,157 --> 00:10:16,119
Oh, right!
Our old roller coaster deal.

157
00:10:16,203 --> 00:10:17,746
- Of course, yeah.
- Phew!

158
00:10:17,830 --> 00:10:20,874
But, uh, we can't go today, lad.

159
00:10:20,958 --> 00:10:23,669
Things are too busy around here.

160
00:10:24,128 --> 00:10:26,755
Oh. Hear that, Patrick? Mr.--

161
00:10:28,715 --> 00:10:30,883
Ow!

162
00:10:30,968 --> 00:10:32,594
Shipwreck!

163
00:10:33,846 --> 00:10:35,931
Thanks for covering for me, Mr. Krabs.

164
00:10:36,014 --> 00:10:39,142
I don't know why I got so scared
when I saw that roller coaster.

165
00:10:39,226 --> 00:10:40,477
I thought I was big enough.

166
00:10:40,561 --> 00:10:43,355
Just 'cause you're taller
don't mean you're a big guy.

167
00:10:43,438 --> 00:10:44,730
It doesn't?

168
00:10:44,815 --> 00:10:46,900
Big guys are rough and tumble.

169
00:10:46,984 --> 00:10:48,151
They don't blow bubbles.

170
00:10:48,235 --> 00:10:50,528
Hmm. I guess not.

171
00:10:50,612 --> 00:10:53,948
Being scared of roller coasters
ain't nothing to be ashamed of.

172
00:10:54,032 --> 00:10:55,408
Glad you understand.

173
00:10:55,492 --> 00:10:57,702
You must've been scared
of roller coasters, too,

174
00:10:57,786 --> 00:11:00,038
- when you were my age.
- Well, I wouldn't really--

175
00:11:00,122 --> 00:11:03,083
You were probably hiding-under-the-bed
kind of scared, weren't you?

176
00:11:03,167 --> 00:11:04,168
Well, I, uh--

177
00:11:04,251 --> 00:11:06,628
Maybe even cwyin'-fo'-Mama
kind of scared.

178
00:11:06,712 --> 00:11:07,754
I wasn't crying for Mama!

179
00:11:07,838 --> 00:11:10,423
Poopy-pee-pee-in-my-pantsy
kind of scared.

180
00:11:10,507 --> 00:11:11,508
Am I right?

181
00:11:11,592 --> 00:11:14,094
Get it straight, SpongeBob!
My pants were clean!

182
00:11:14,178 --> 00:11:17,389
'Cause nothing ever scared me...
and nothing ever will!

183
00:11:17,472 --> 00:11:20,433
But didn't you say being scared
wasn't anything to be ashamed of?

184
00:11:20,517 --> 00:11:22,602
It ain't! For you.

185
00:11:22,686 --> 00:11:26,439
But I'm different.
I wasn't blowing bubbles at your age.

186
00:11:26,523 --> 00:11:28,024
I was risking me life

187
00:11:28,108 --> 00:11:29,651
on the high seas!

188
00:11:31,612 --> 00:11:34,406
I ate danger for breakfast!
Peril for lunch!

189
00:11:34,489 --> 00:11:36,407
And adventure for dinner!

190
00:11:36,491 --> 00:11:39,619
- Wha-what? -what? Really?
- That's right!

191
00:11:39,703 --> 00:11:42,497
I was in command of me own vessel,

192
00:11:42,581 --> 00:11:45,375
<i>and sailed many a dangerous mile.</i>

193
00:11:45,876 --> 00:11:48,086
Tell me about your greatest adventure.

194
00:11:48,170 --> 00:11:52,670
What if I told you I sailed
with the Flying Dutchman himself?

195
00:11:53,258 --> 00:11:54,842
The Flying Dutchman?

196
00:11:54,927 --> 00:11:57,554
The most pants-wettingly
scariest ghost

197
00:11:57,638 --> 00:11:59,681
to ever roam the high seas?

198
00:12:00,515 --> 00:12:02,099
Oh, my lucky brick.

199
00:12:02,184 --> 00:12:03,185
Aye!

200
00:12:03,268 --> 00:12:07,438
<i>Like many a young sailor before me,
I longed for adventure.</i>

201
00:12:11,735 --> 00:12:15,488
<i>And that's when
the Dutchman's hornpipe appeared.</i>

202
00:12:18,575 --> 00:12:20,451
<i>I summoned
the cursed pirate,</i>

203
00:12:20,535 --> 00:12:23,829
<i>and journeyed with him
to the deepest part of the sea.</i>

204
00:12:23,914 --> 00:12:25,040
<i>A nightmare realm</i>

205
00:12:25,123 --> 00:12:28,626
<i>called the Underworld.</i>

206
00:12:29,795 --> 00:12:32,088
It was filled
with ghostly pirates,

207
00:12:32,172 --> 00:12:34,257
<i>haunted hurricanes,</i>

208
00:12:34,341 --> 00:12:36,885
<i>terrifying monsters!</i>

209
00:12:38,220 --> 00:12:39,262
Roar!

210
00:12:39,346 --> 00:12:40,513
Whoa!

211
00:12:40,597 --> 00:12:42,849
I faced 'em all
with steel in me backbone

212
00:12:42,933 --> 00:12:45,602
<i>and a cutlass in me claw!</i>

213
00:12:45,686 --> 00:12:47,062
<i>Hyah!</i>

214
00:12:47,145 --> 00:12:48,479
<i>Hoo-waa!</i>

215
00:12:48,563 --> 00:12:51,232
<i>Hyah!</i>

216
00:12:51,316 --> 00:12:55,486
<i>It was the greatest adventure
of me life!</i>

217
00:12:55,570 --> 00:12:57,113
Wow!

218
00:12:57,698 --> 00:13:00,325
You're almost like
a real swashbuckler!

219
00:13:00,409 --> 00:13:03,954
Almost? I am a real swashbuckler!

220
00:13:04,037 --> 00:13:06,039
How do you think I earned this baby?

221
00:13:06,123 --> 00:13:07,499
What is that?

222
00:13:07,582 --> 00:13:10,126
It's a Swashbuckler Certificate.

223
00:13:10,210 --> 00:13:12,086
It means I proved my bravery,

224
00:13:12,170 --> 00:13:14,714
courageousness, daring, panache,

225
00:13:14,798 --> 00:13:16,382
guts, grit,

226
00:13:16,466 --> 00:13:17,717
moxie,

227
00:13:17,801 --> 00:13:20,553
and intestinal fortitude.

228
00:13:20,637 --> 00:13:21,888
Well, that's it!

229
00:13:21,972 --> 00:13:25,517
I'd be a big guy if I could earn
my Swashbuckler Certificate.

230
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:28,060
And you could teach me!

231
00:13:28,145 --> 00:13:30,689
Teach you? To be a swashbuckler?

232
00:13:30,772 --> 00:13:32,648
I don't mean to laugh
in your face, but...

233
00:13:36,486 --> 00:13:39,238
You're too scared
to even ride a roller coaster!

234
00:13:39,323 --> 00:13:40,490
I can do it.

235
00:13:40,574 --> 00:13:43,743
I want to be a brave swashbuckler
like you.

236
00:13:43,827 --> 00:13:44,953
I'm ready.

237
00:13:45,037 --> 00:13:48,665
SpongeBob, you're just
a bubble-blowing baby boy

238
00:13:48,749 --> 00:13:50,292
who's not ready.

239
00:13:50,375 --> 00:13:52,585
- But... But... But--
- Butts are for toilets!

240
00:13:52,669 --> 00:13:55,296
Speaking of which,
the heads need swabbing, so git!

241
00:13:55,380 --> 00:13:58,674
And no more talk
about being a swashbuckler.

242
00:13:58,759 --> 00:14:00,051
Aww.

243
00:14:01,428 --> 00:14:04,055
You're not ready...
not ready... not ready...

244
00:14:04,139 --> 00:14:06,808
not ready... not ready...
not ready... not ready!

245
00:14:13,982 --> 00:14:15,566
Bravery. Courage.

246
00:14:15,650 --> 00:14:19,070
I got to learn this stuff if I'm gonna
prove myself to Mr. Krabs.

247
00:14:19,154 --> 00:14:21,406
You got this, SpongeBob.

248
00:14:21,948 --> 00:14:23,449
Uh-oh.

249
00:14:23,533 --> 00:14:25,451
Now what else did he say I needed?

250
00:14:25,535 --> 00:14:27,286
- Daring.
- Oh, right. Daring.

251
00:14:27,371 --> 00:14:28,830
- Guts.
- Definitely need those.

252
00:14:28,914 --> 00:14:31,833
Panache.
Moxie. Intestinal fortitude.

253
00:14:31,917 --> 00:14:34,419
- Okay, okay! Slow down!
- You spelled "fortitude" wrong.

254
00:14:34,503 --> 00:14:37,672
It's F-O-R-T-l-T-U-D-E.

255
00:14:37,756 --> 00:14:39,299
Mr. Krabs's certificate!

256
00:14:39,383 --> 00:14:43,095
- Why do you have this?
- I always read in the bathroom.

257
00:14:43,178 --> 00:14:45,930
I know I can do this.

258
00:14:46,014 --> 00:14:47,807
I just need a chance to prove it!

259
00:14:47,891 --> 00:14:49,934
<i>Prove it...</i>

260
00:15:00,028 --> 00:15:02,113
Well, that's weird.

261
00:15:05,033 --> 00:15:07,785
Oh, shrimp! The certificate!

262
00:15:08,370 --> 00:15:10,497
Mr. Krabs won't like that.

263
00:15:10,580 --> 00:15:13,207
- Oh, we got to get it, right?
- Uh, I'm not going in there.

264
00:15:13,792 --> 00:15:16,753
Yeah, you'd have to be pretty brave
to go in there.

265
00:15:16,837 --> 00:15:18,129
Hey, wait a minute!

266
00:15:18,213 --> 00:15:20,548
- Patrick, this is it!
- It is?

267
00:15:20,632 --> 00:15:24,052
Destiny is squeezing my buns.

268
00:15:24,136 --> 00:15:25,345
Do you feel it?

269
00:15:25,429 --> 00:15:26,680
Yeah!

270
00:15:27,514 --> 00:15:29,349
This vent is just what I need

271
00:15:29,433 --> 00:15:31,893
to start earning my
Swashbuckler Certificate.

272
00:15:31,977 --> 00:15:33,436
You mean the one we lost?

273
00:15:33,520 --> 00:15:36,189
Oh, yes, that one,
but also the one I'm gonna earn.

274
00:15:36,273 --> 00:15:38,024
We lost two of them down there?

275
00:15:39,151 --> 00:15:43,071
The hero's journey
starts with one squish.

276
00:15:46,491 --> 00:15:48,034
Right behind you.

277
00:15:50,871 --> 00:15:52,163
I'll catch up.

278
00:15:54,624 --> 00:15:57,001
Ooh. Side adventure.

279
00:15:59,671 --> 00:16:04,092
- Hmm. Left or right?
- Hmm.

280
00:16:04,176 --> 00:16:06,094
Left! Definitely left!

281
00:16:10,056 --> 00:16:11,640
Ow!

282
00:16:16,813 --> 00:16:19,023
This must lead to the basement.

283
00:16:19,107 --> 00:16:21,275
This must go deeper than the basement.

284
00:16:24,488 --> 00:16:25,489
Wha--

285
00:16:26,740 --> 00:16:28,074
Where am I?

286
00:16:37,876 --> 00:16:40,044
Wow!

287
00:16:40,587 --> 00:16:45,008
This must be Mr. Krabs's
swashbuckler sanctum.

288
00:16:45,091 --> 00:16:47,718
Whoa, look at that.

289
00:16:47,802 --> 00:16:48,844
And that.

290
00:16:48,929 --> 00:16:53,429
And that! And that! And that!
And that! And that! And that!

291
00:16:55,810 --> 00:16:56,811
Hi.

292
00:16:59,731 --> 00:17:02,316
- Argh!
- Ahoy!

293
00:17:09,741 --> 00:17:14,120
So, who's a bubble-blowing
baby boy now, huh?

294
00:17:21,461 --> 00:17:22,587
Whoa!

295
00:17:31,346 --> 00:17:33,097
Oh, who am I kidding?

296
00:17:33,181 --> 00:17:35,808
I'll never be a swashbuckler.

297
00:17:39,020 --> 00:17:40,021
Hmm?

298
00:17:43,733 --> 00:17:46,694
Mysterious Glow...

299
00:17:46,778 --> 00:17:48,029
Part Two.

300
00:17:51,116 --> 00:17:52,700
Whoa.

301
00:17:52,784 --> 00:17:55,703
This must be the hornpipe
Mr. Krabs took

302
00:17:55,787 --> 00:17:57,288
from the Flying Dutchman!

303
00:17:58,540 --> 00:18:01,543
"If a swashbuckler ye want to be,

304
00:18:02,127 --> 00:18:05,046
"blow this horn and ye shall see."

305
00:18:05,130 --> 00:18:08,383
Patrick,
I'm feeling destiny again.

306
00:18:10,260 --> 00:18:13,263
Still nothing.
But don't let me slow you down.

307
00:18:34,659 --> 00:18:37,703
Huh? That sounds like... Oh, no!

308
00:18:39,706 --> 00:18:41,124
Huh?

309
00:18:41,207 --> 00:18:44,418
SpongeBob! Get out of there!

310
00:18:44,502 --> 00:18:46,629
Have fun.

311
00:19:10,904 --> 00:19:12,572
Land ho!

312
00:19:24,918 --> 00:19:26,628
Uh, you dropped your lucky brick.

313
00:19:26,711 --> 00:19:28,421
I don't have a lucky brick.

314
00:19:33,176 --> 00:19:36,053
On your feet,
ya sea-drinkin' polliwog!

315
00:19:36,137 --> 00:19:38,264
You're in the company

316
00:19:38,848 --> 00:19:41,183
of the Flying Dutchman!

317
00:19:46,815 --> 00:19:48,358
Hmm.

318
00:19:50,193 --> 00:19:53,654
Who blew my hornpipe?

319
00:19:55,073 --> 00:19:57,450
Uh... I did.

320
00:19:57,534 --> 00:19:58,826
Hmm.

321
00:19:58,910 --> 00:20:02,038
SpongeBob, I'm comin'!

322
00:20:02,122 --> 00:20:04,457
<i>Hurry! Hurry! Hurry!</i>

323
00:20:05,291 --> 00:20:06,834
Weird place for a painting.

324
00:20:06,918 --> 00:20:07,960
Move it, Squidward!

325
00:20:08,044 --> 00:20:09,837
<i>Hurry! Hurry!
Hurry! Hurry!</i>

326
00:20:09,921 --> 00:20:12,965
Ah, let me take a look at ya.

327
00:20:13,049 --> 00:20:17,549
Spit-shine shoes. Long socks.
Short pants.

328
00:20:18,054 --> 00:20:20,681
Empty middle-distant stare.

329
00:20:20,765 --> 00:20:24,226
Tell me, laddie, can ya blow a bubble?

330
00:20:27,564 --> 00:20:28,773
Why...

331
00:20:29,274 --> 00:20:33,444
you're the very swab
I've been lookin' for!

332
00:20:33,528 --> 00:20:35,655
Really?

333
00:20:35,739 --> 00:20:39,492
You look the kind of strappin' young
bubble-blowin' fella who wants...

334
00:20:39,576 --> 00:20:43,621
nay, needs a chance
to prove his mettle.

335
00:20:43,705 --> 00:20:47,166
He was just saying that
in the bathroom!

336
00:20:47,250 --> 00:20:48,501
Quiet! You don't matter.

337
00:20:48,585 --> 00:20:49,669
Very good.

338
00:20:49,753 --> 00:20:51,880
That's why I blew the horn,
Mr. Dutchman, sir.

339
00:20:51,963 --> 00:20:53,381
I need to prove I'm a big guy

340
00:20:53,465 --> 00:20:56,176
by earning my
Swashbuckler Certificate.

341
00:20:56,259 --> 00:21:00,759
Well, I'm here to offer you
a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity

342
00:21:01,556 --> 00:21:05,226
to prove your worth in the Underworld.

343
00:21:05,310 --> 00:21:07,729
Just like Mr. Krabs!

344
00:21:07,812 --> 00:21:10,898
Aw. But he doesn't think
I'm ready for that kind of thing.

345
00:21:10,982 --> 00:21:13,484
Well, maybe he's right.

346
00:21:13,568 --> 00:21:15,820
You might not be ready for...

347
00:21:15,904 --> 00:21:17,906
swashbucklin'!

348
00:21:17,989 --> 00:21:20,282
Swashbuckling?

349
00:21:20,366 --> 00:21:22,743
Swashbucklin'.

350
00:21:33,046 --> 00:21:35,214
Swashbuckling!

351
00:21:40,011 --> 00:21:41,512
Ah!

352
00:21:53,233 --> 00:21:54,442
Huh?

353
00:21:57,987 --> 00:21:59,029
Whoa!

354
00:22:06,162 --> 00:22:08,330
I'm ready!

355
00:22:08,414 --> 00:22:10,582
Then it's a deal.

356
00:22:10,667 --> 00:22:12,919
The Dutchman's deal.

357
00:22:30,019 --> 00:22:31,562
Stupid passcode.

358
00:22:32,480 --> 00:22:34,315
Four... fifteen... eight.

359
00:22:36,150 --> 00:22:38,026
Permission to come aboard, sir!

360
00:22:38,111 --> 00:22:39,987
Granted, shipmate!

361
00:22:40,071 --> 00:22:43,449
- Me, too?
- Only if ya put on some pants.

362
00:22:44,033 --> 00:22:45,743
I guess.

363
00:22:47,453 --> 00:22:48,495
Pupil scan?

364
00:22:50,999 --> 00:22:52,041
- Ooh!
- Whee!

365
00:22:52,125 --> 00:22:54,252
Welcome aboard!

366
00:22:56,921 --> 00:22:59,298
Blast these long eyes.

367
00:22:59,382 --> 00:23:00,383
Come on.

368
00:23:00,466 --> 00:23:02,926
Right this way to your quarters.

369
00:23:03,011 --> 00:23:06,723
I'm gonna be a swashbuckler. Yeah!

370
00:23:06,806 --> 00:23:08,349
What do ya think, Captain?

371
00:23:08,433 --> 00:23:11,602
Pure heart, innocent mind,

372
00:23:11,686 --> 00:23:14,146
desperate to be a big guy.

373
00:23:14,230 --> 00:23:15,898
He's perfect.

374
00:23:18,568 --> 00:23:20,528
Ahoy, Krabs!

375
00:23:20,612 --> 00:23:23,323
Long time no see!

376
00:23:23,406 --> 00:23:26,117
Please, don't take SpongeBob!

377
00:23:26,200 --> 00:23:29,620
You'll never see him again.

378
00:23:29,704 --> 00:23:32,873
He's the key to unlocking my curse.

379
00:23:32,957 --> 00:23:37,457
SpongeBob!

380
00:23:46,471 --> 00:23:48,931
Cinch up your trousers, me hearties.

381
00:23:49,015 --> 00:23:53,477
A trip to the Underworld
is not for the faint of heart.

382
00:24:08,284 --> 00:24:11,787
Oh, Squidward, what are we gonna do?

383
00:24:11,871 --> 00:24:14,164
Sorry, I don't speak "do."

384
00:24:14,248 --> 00:24:16,333
All me blusterin' and braggin',

385
00:24:16,417 --> 00:24:18,460
fillin' that boy's head
with adventure!

386
00:24:18,544 --> 00:24:22,381
I drove him right into
the tender mercies of that monster,

387
00:24:22,465 --> 00:24:24,383
the Flying Dutchman.

388
00:24:24,467 --> 00:24:27,303
Look, Eugene,
you can't blame yourself.

389
00:24:27,387 --> 00:24:28,388
Mr. Krabs.

390
00:24:28,471 --> 00:24:30,723
- Say what?
- Call me Mr. Krabs.

391
00:24:30,807 --> 00:24:32,266
Okay.

392
00:24:32,350 --> 00:24:35,561
- Look, "Mr. Krabs"...
- There ya go.

393
00:24:35,645 --> 00:24:38,814
- You know what? It is your fault.
- You're right, Squidward.

394
00:24:38,898 --> 00:24:42,192
- Which is why we got to go save him!
- Hold it.

395
00:24:42,276 --> 00:24:44,778
You don't think
I'm actually participating

396
00:24:44,862 --> 00:24:46,572
in this fool's errand, do you?

397
00:24:46,656 --> 00:24:48,324
I know you are.

398
00:24:48,408 --> 00:24:52,908
Because if you don't, I'll demote you
to fry cook. Permanently!

399
00:24:52,996 --> 00:24:56,207
But the grease inflames my acne!

400
00:25:11,389 --> 00:25:15,059
So, just the two of us
against the Dutchman, huh?

401
00:25:15,143 --> 00:25:17,687
There's three in this crew,
Mr. Squidward.

402
00:25:19,230 --> 00:25:21,315
- Meow.
- Why was I worried?

403
00:25:21,399 --> 00:25:24,402
Nice to see
me old gear still fits, eh?

404
00:25:28,239 --> 00:25:29,615
Squawk!

405
00:25:29,699 --> 00:25:31,033
What the-- Huh?

406
00:25:31,993 --> 00:25:35,871
Hmm. Not bad.

407
00:25:35,955 --> 00:25:40,209
And to get us there in style,
say hello to our noble vessel,

408
00:25:40,293 --> 00:25:42,878
The Patty Blaster!

409
00:25:42,962 --> 00:25:47,049
Hey, we might actually be safe
on this adventure, driving a...

410
00:25:49,385 --> 00:25:51,095
Winnebago.

411
00:25:51,179 --> 00:25:55,679
We can't lose in a "Win" -nebago,
Mr. Squidward.

412
00:25:56,517 --> 00:25:57,643
Hilarious.

413
00:25:57,727 --> 00:25:59,228
Squawk! Hilarious!

414
00:25:59,312 --> 00:26:02,189
Do you even know
how to find SpongeBob?

415
00:26:02,273 --> 00:26:04,400
Aye, Squidward, but it won't be easy.

416
00:26:04,484 --> 00:26:06,486
The Dutchman's taken SpongeBob
to the deepest,

417
00:26:06,569 --> 00:26:08,696
most dangerous part of the sea.

418
00:26:09,739 --> 00:26:13,826
A realm of dark magic
called the Underworld.

419
00:26:13,910 --> 00:26:14,911
Under where?

420
00:26:15,620 --> 00:26:17,163
Underwear.

421
00:26:18,372 --> 00:26:20,457
Well, how do we get there?

422
00:26:20,541 --> 00:26:23,377
First we've got to find
the magical portal.

423
00:26:23,461 --> 00:26:27,961
Then navigate the Slime River
through unimaginable terrors.

424
00:26:28,049 --> 00:26:32,344
And if we survive,
this is where we find SpongeBob.

425
00:26:32,428 --> 00:26:33,720
Meow!

426
00:26:33,805 --> 00:26:35,598
Challenge Cove?

427
00:26:35,681 --> 00:26:39,309
That's where the Dutchman
can use SpongeBob to break his curse!

428
00:26:39,393 --> 00:26:42,187
And if we don't get down there in time
to stop him,

429
00:26:42,271 --> 00:26:45,399
our favorite fry cook
is doomed!

430
00:26:45,483 --> 00:26:49,653
Now saddle up!
We got no time to waste!

431
00:27:00,331 --> 00:27:01,332
Full disclosure,

432
00:27:01,415 --> 00:27:03,083
that's farther than I thought
we'd get.

433
00:27:04,460 --> 00:27:06,044
Pop the clutch, Gary!

434
00:27:08,548 --> 00:27:10,091
Whoo-hoo!

435
00:27:23,938 --> 00:27:27,983
Welcome to the Underworld!

436
00:27:32,155 --> 00:27:33,156
Huh?

437
00:27:38,202 --> 00:27:40,746
Maybe I'm not ready for this place.

438
00:27:40,830 --> 00:27:45,330
Ah, yes, the Underworld
can be terrifying to most.

439
00:27:45,418 --> 00:27:49,213
But not to a brave big guy
like yourself.

440
00:27:49,297 --> 00:27:51,465
You think I'm brave?

441
00:27:51,549 --> 00:27:53,676
Aye, you laugh at danger!

442
00:27:58,848 --> 00:28:01,433
I mean...

443
00:28:01,517 --> 00:28:03,227
You can do better than that.

444
00:28:05,313 --> 00:28:07,440
I can't hear you.

445
00:28:12,570 --> 00:28:14,238
Don't worry, Patrick.

446
00:28:14,322 --> 00:28:16,657
We laugh at danger!

447
00:28:18,409 --> 00:28:20,035
Huh? Huh?

448
00:28:23,623 --> 00:28:24,624
Huh?

449
00:28:26,042 --> 00:28:27,168
Incoming!

450
00:28:28,753 --> 00:28:30,838
Whoo-hoo!

451
00:28:42,516 --> 00:28:43,767
Whoo!

452
00:28:46,229 --> 00:28:49,398
- Ooh!
- Wow!

453
00:28:54,987 --> 00:28:56,154
Uh... Huh?

454
00:29:07,708 --> 00:29:11,670
You were right, Dutchman.
I'm not afraid of the Underworld!

455
00:29:12,838 --> 00:29:14,923
Glad to hear it, lad.

456
00:29:15,007 --> 00:29:16,925
I'm not afraid, either!

457
00:29:17,009 --> 00:29:18,051
Who cares?

458
00:29:18,135 --> 00:29:22,635
SpongeBob, I want you to think of me
as your swashbuckling guru,

459
00:29:23,724 --> 00:29:26,351
and your friend.

460
00:29:26,435 --> 00:29:27,436
Aw.

461
00:29:27,520 --> 00:29:29,355
Look! More danger!

462
00:29:29,438 --> 00:29:31,356
Here, kitty, kitty.

463
00:29:31,440 --> 00:29:32,732
Nyah-ah!

464
00:29:40,700 --> 00:29:44,078
Captain, this lubber
is a complete barnacle brain.

465
00:29:44,161 --> 00:29:46,204
Are you sure he's the one?

466
00:29:46,289 --> 00:29:50,251
True, he don't have physical prowess
or pirating ability,

467
00:29:50,334 --> 00:29:53,795
but the boy's got
the very thing we need...

468
00:29:55,673 --> 00:29:58,050
Staggering stupidity.

469
00:29:58,134 --> 00:30:01,971
He won't figure out the truth
until it's way too late,

470
00:30:02,054 --> 00:30:06,308
when we finally break my curse!

471
00:30:06,392 --> 00:30:09,103
Break your curse!

472
00:30:09,186 --> 00:30:11,104
My curse!

473
00:30:11,188 --> 00:30:13,356
Your curse!

474
00:30:17,653 --> 00:30:19,196
What are we laughing about?

475
00:30:20,281 --> 00:30:22,408
Oh, uh, nothin', lad.

476
00:30:28,622 --> 00:30:29,789
Accordin' to the map,

477
00:30:29,874 --> 00:30:34,374
the gates to the Underworld lie
in the most horrible place imaginable.

478
00:30:40,384 --> 00:30:42,469
Bikini Bottom High.

479
00:30:42,553 --> 00:30:45,681
- Aye, dangerous waters.
- Ew.

480
00:30:45,765 --> 00:30:48,934
- Nice ride.
- Losers.

481
00:30:49,018 --> 00:30:50,269
See what I mean?

482
00:30:52,063 --> 00:30:53,522
Hey!

483
00:30:58,277 --> 00:31:00,279
Yeah!

484
00:31:00,363 --> 00:31:03,074
- Whoa! Whoa!
- Ahh!

485
00:31:03,157 --> 00:31:05,742
- Whoa!
- Ahh!

486
00:31:07,328 --> 00:31:09,079
Right! Take a right!

487
00:31:12,833 --> 00:31:13,834
Hmph!

488
00:31:13,918 --> 00:31:16,420
Is that Squidward Tentacles?

489
00:31:16,962 --> 00:31:18,505
Coach Tuna?

490
00:31:18,589 --> 00:31:21,174
You still owe me laps.

491
00:31:21,258 --> 00:31:22,968
Incoming fire!

492
00:31:27,431 --> 00:31:28,723
- Ah!
- Squawk!

493
00:31:28,808 --> 00:31:30,434
Hah.

494
00:31:32,603 --> 00:31:34,605
Huh?

495
00:31:35,856 --> 00:31:36,898
Hey!

496
00:31:36,982 --> 00:31:37,983
Ow!

497
00:31:38,067 --> 00:31:39,526
Meow! Meow! Meow!

498
00:31:39,610 --> 00:31:41,403
Huh?

499
00:31:46,075 --> 00:31:47,701
We're close.

500
00:31:48,244 --> 00:31:50,913
I can smell it.

501
00:31:50,996 --> 00:31:52,372
Me, too.

502
00:31:57,420 --> 00:31:59,547
Are you Davy?

503
00:31:59,630 --> 00:32:02,799
No, man, I'm Phil. Davy's over there.

504
00:32:03,467 --> 00:32:05,218
Thar she blows!

505
00:32:05,302 --> 00:32:07,554
Davy Jones' locker.

506
00:32:07,638 --> 00:32:10,265
The entrance to the Underworld.

507
00:32:29,076 --> 00:32:31,328
If you're
gonna be a swashbuckler,

508
00:32:31,412 --> 00:32:34,623
you got to dress the part.

509
00:32:35,791 --> 00:32:39,252
Now step out, lad.
Let's get a look at ya.

510
00:32:41,547 --> 00:32:44,633
Are you sure this is
a swashbuckler outfit?

511
00:32:44,717 --> 00:32:47,177
Absolutely! Standard issue.

512
00:32:47,261 --> 00:32:49,638
Really? Wh-- Whoa!

513
00:32:49,722 --> 00:32:53,267
That safety suit
should keep him alive long enough

514
00:32:53,350 --> 00:32:55,143
to break my curse.

515
00:32:55,227 --> 00:32:57,520
Your curse.

516
00:32:57,605 --> 00:32:59,982
Come on, Barb... read the room.

517
00:33:00,065 --> 00:33:01,191
Hold it!

518
00:33:01,692 --> 00:33:04,528
No! No, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no, no!

519
00:33:04,612 --> 00:33:07,865
This is all wrong!
Let's find something else.

520
00:33:07,948 --> 00:33:09,449
Wait! Mind your business!

521
00:33:14,163 --> 00:33:17,374
Fashion show! This feels much better.

522
00:33:17,458 --> 00:33:20,335
I don't think that's quite right, lad.

523
00:33:20,419 --> 00:33:24,297
I agree, Dutchie.
It's missing one thing.

524
00:33:27,968 --> 00:33:29,469
Achoo!

525
00:33:31,013 --> 00:33:33,348
Pink guy's drivin' me nuts!

526
00:33:33,432 --> 00:33:37,227
He's distracting the fool.
Their friendship is a problem.

527
00:33:37,311 --> 00:33:40,647
That's why we work
so well together, Barb.

528
00:33:40,731 --> 00:33:42,607
We've never been friends.

529
00:33:42,691 --> 00:33:45,110
Exactly! I-- Wait, what?

530
00:33:45,194 --> 00:33:47,779
Yeah, we'll have to take care

531
00:33:47,863 --> 00:33:49,197
of that one.

532
00:33:50,741 --> 00:33:51,742
Land ho!

533
00:33:52,701 --> 00:33:53,868
Whoa!

534
00:33:53,953 --> 00:33:55,204
Whoa!

535
00:33:56,288 --> 00:33:58,206
<i>Whoa</i>

536
00:33:58,791 --> 00:34:01,835
We've arrived at Challenge Cove.

537
00:34:01,919 --> 00:34:05,923
The place where you'll finally
become a swashbuckler.

538
00:34:06,006 --> 00:34:07,007
Whoo-hoo!

539
00:34:24,024 --> 00:34:25,233
Meow.

540
00:34:25,317 --> 00:34:27,235
Are you sure about this?

541
00:34:27,319 --> 00:34:30,655
Don't worry, Mr. Squidward.
I've got everything under control.

542
00:34:33,909 --> 00:34:37,120
These creatures
look friendly enough, huh?

543
00:34:41,458 --> 00:34:44,919
That was the scariest thing
I ever saw!

544
00:34:45,504 --> 00:34:46,505
Till I saw that.

545
00:34:58,434 --> 00:34:59,435
- Huh?
- Huh?

546
00:35:04,106 --> 00:35:06,149
Meow.

547
00:35:06,233 --> 00:35:10,733
Here's an idea. We go home
and you hire a new fry cook!

548
00:35:13,073 --> 00:35:14,574
What do you think, Gary?

549
00:35:18,954 --> 00:35:23,083
SpongeBob's first Krusty Krab ID card.

550
00:35:23,167 --> 00:35:26,670
Look at him. So... yellow.

551
00:35:26,754 --> 00:35:28,464
That answers that.

552
00:35:33,302 --> 00:35:35,512
Is that where we have to go?

553
00:35:35,596 --> 00:35:39,433
Aye!
To succeed, you must reach that X.

554
00:35:39,516 --> 00:35:41,643
And then I'll get my certificate!

555
00:35:41,727 --> 00:35:45,355
Right after you make it up
to the next X.

556
00:35:45,439 --> 00:35:48,650
And then up to that one.
And up to the next one.

557
00:35:48,734 --> 00:35:50,569
And then up again. And up there.

558
00:35:50,653 --> 00:35:52,071
How high do I have to go?

559
00:35:52,154 --> 00:35:53,405
To the top, lad!

560
00:35:53,489 --> 00:35:55,616
If you make it there
and blow that hornpipe,

561
00:35:55,699 --> 00:35:58,618
oh, you'll become a swashbuckler.

562
00:35:58,702 --> 00:36:01,204
Mr. Krabs will be so proud!

563
00:36:01,747 --> 00:36:05,667
- If I can do it.
- No, it'll be easy!

564
00:36:05,751 --> 00:36:08,879
We'll get through
these challenges together.

565
00:36:09,296 --> 00:36:11,506
Starting with, uh, oh...

566
00:36:11,590 --> 00:36:14,009
intestinal fortitude.

567
00:36:14,093 --> 00:36:17,638
To begin,
we'll walk that path until we--

568
00:36:17,721 --> 00:36:20,223
Not so fast!

569
00:36:22,434 --> 00:36:25,770
You said we have to walk this path.

570
00:36:25,854 --> 00:36:30,354
But this is clearly a road.

571
00:36:32,403 --> 00:36:35,781
- You're right, Patrick. It is a road.
- I know.

572
00:36:35,864 --> 00:36:37,031
Tartar sauce!

573
00:36:37,116 --> 00:36:38,200
Now what are we gonna do?

574
00:36:38,283 --> 00:36:39,367
I know.

575
00:36:39,451 --> 00:36:40,785
What difference does it make?

576
00:36:40,869 --> 00:36:43,037
You say "road," I say "path."

577
00:36:43,122 --> 00:36:45,457
I say "potato," you say "po-tah-to!"

578
00:36:45,541 --> 00:36:47,876
No, I don't. I say "string cheese."

579
00:36:47,960 --> 00:36:48,961
Ooh.

580
00:36:49,044 --> 00:36:52,547
- String cheese.
- String cheese.

581
00:36:52,631 --> 00:36:56,509
- String cheese.
- A road of string cheese.

582
00:36:56,593 --> 00:37:01,093
- String Cheese Road!
- String Cheese... Expressway!

583
00:37:01,223 --> 00:37:03,308
String Cheese... Castle!

584
00:37:03,392 --> 00:37:04,518
I can't take it!

585
00:37:04,601 --> 00:37:07,145
Barb, no!
Killing him might tip him off.

586
00:37:07,229 --> 00:37:11,358
What do you say we go beat
these challenges, road or no road?

587
00:37:13,318 --> 00:37:14,444
Wait!

588
00:37:14,528 --> 00:37:17,614
Watch out for the Skeleton Guardians!

589
00:37:17,698 --> 00:37:19,366
- Huh?
- What?

590
00:37:19,450 --> 00:37:21,994
Watch out for the-- what? -oof--

591
00:37:22,077 --> 00:37:24,662
Watch out for the what?
- oof?

592
00:37:24,747 --> 00:37:25,748
Not sure what that means.

593
00:37:25,831 --> 00:37:30,331
Plus, it's hard to hear with all the
"cck-oo-cck-oo-cck-oo" sounds.

594
00:37:30,502 --> 00:37:32,879
Well, whatever it is,
I'm sure it's not that important.

595
00:37:36,383 --> 00:37:39,552
Patrick, I think these are the guys
who are gonna...

596
00:37:39,636 --> 00:37:42,263
fortify our intestines!

597
00:37:42,347 --> 00:37:43,348
Yay!

598
00:37:45,309 --> 00:37:49,104
Barb, we got to reach that nitwit
before he gets killed!

599
00:37:49,188 --> 00:37:51,190
Desperately trying, sir!

600
00:37:51,690 --> 00:37:55,610
What do you think, path or road?

601
00:37:57,529 --> 00:38:01,282
Can someone
hand me my eyebrows?

602
00:38:01,366 --> 00:38:05,328
Swordplay, huh?
I think my skills will satisfy.

603
00:38:06,955 --> 00:38:10,291
Dodge! Parry! Thrust! Plié.

604
00:38:13,170 --> 00:38:14,296
Patrick!

605
00:38:22,221 --> 00:38:24,014
What if Mr. Krabs was right

606
00:38:24,097 --> 00:38:26,766
and I am just
a bubble-blowing baby boy?

607
00:38:26,850 --> 00:38:28,393
That wouldn't be good.

608
00:38:28,477 --> 00:38:30,562
Oh, Patrick, what are we gonna do?

609
00:38:37,319 --> 00:38:40,780
Yer askin'
the wrong question, lad!

610
00:38:40,864 --> 00:38:42,824
Mr. Krabs?

611
00:38:43,534 --> 00:38:45,702
If ya want to get out of this pickle,

612
00:38:45,786 --> 00:38:50,286
you're gonna have to start actin'
like a rough-and-tumble swashbuckler.

613
00:38:50,624 --> 00:38:52,125
Well, how do I do that?

614
00:38:52,209 --> 00:38:55,670
Ya start by askin' the right question.

615
00:38:55,754 --> 00:38:58,715
It's not,
"What are we gonna do?"

616
00:38:58,799 --> 00:39:01,635
It's, "What would I do?"

617
00:39:01,718 --> 00:39:04,011
What would I do?

618
00:39:04,096 --> 00:39:05,931
Huh? No. No, no. Me!

619
00:39:06,014 --> 00:39:07,724
What would me do?

620
00:39:07,808 --> 00:39:10,894
Not you. Me! Mr. Krabs!

621
00:39:10,978 --> 00:39:12,771
What would I do?

622
00:39:12,855 --> 00:39:15,566
Oh! That makes way more sense.

623
00:39:22,531 --> 00:39:25,367
So, how does it-- Does this end or--

624
00:39:25,450 --> 00:39:26,534
Wake up!

625
00:39:26,618 --> 00:39:29,871
Patrick,
maybe if we act like Mr. Krabs,

626
00:39:29,955 --> 00:39:31,539
we can make our way through this.

627
00:39:31,623 --> 00:39:33,374
Why didn't I think of that?

628
00:39:33,458 --> 00:39:37,958
Because you're not a Swashbuckler
Certificate recipient in the making!

629
00:39:38,171 --> 00:39:40,673
Barb! Do ya spy the barnacle?

630
00:39:40,757 --> 00:39:43,509
Sorry, sir. I don't-- Wait.

631
00:39:43,594 --> 00:39:46,054
- Hey, look at me!
- Huh?

632
00:39:52,436 --> 00:39:55,939
Argh.
I'm no bubble blower.

633
00:39:56,023 --> 00:39:58,942
I'm a rough-and-tumble swashbuckler.

634
00:39:59,026 --> 00:40:01,695
Rough and tumble as the day is long.

635
00:40:01,778 --> 00:40:04,697
They don't come
as rough and tumble as me.

636
00:40:04,781 --> 00:40:07,200
Rough and tumble, tumble and--

637
00:40:14,166 --> 00:40:16,251
Huh.

638
00:40:16,335 --> 00:40:17,502
Look at me!

639
00:40:17,586 --> 00:40:20,255
Rumble and tumble!

640
00:40:24,718 --> 00:40:28,138
SpongeBob? These look like...

641
00:40:28,221 --> 00:40:30,223
...our intestines.

642
00:40:30,307 --> 00:40:33,143
And they're fortified!

643
00:40:33,226 --> 00:40:36,062
This means
I passed the first challenge!

644
00:40:36,146 --> 00:40:37,313
Whoo-hoo!

645
00:40:37,397 --> 00:40:38,689
- Look at mine wiggle.
- Huh?

646
00:40:38,774 --> 00:40:41,193
Look at them. Wiggle, wobble!

647
00:40:41,860 --> 00:40:42,861
Peekaboo!

648
00:40:42,945 --> 00:40:45,447
Hairdo-do!

649
00:40:48,033 --> 00:40:50,410
What are those idiots doing?

650
00:40:55,332 --> 00:40:57,584
What is happening?

651
00:41:12,432 --> 00:41:14,517
I don't know
how he did it, Barb.

652
00:41:14,601 --> 00:41:17,562
That fool must really be the one.

653
00:41:17,646 --> 00:41:19,939
I think you're right, sir. Look.

654
00:41:25,028 --> 00:41:26,195
Yes?

655
00:41:27,155 --> 00:41:28,156
Whoa!

656
00:41:28,240 --> 00:41:29,491
Yes?

657
00:41:31,994 --> 00:41:35,664
Yes!

658
00:41:40,836 --> 00:41:41,837
Huh?

659
00:41:41,920 --> 00:41:43,713
- SpongeBob?
- Uh-oh.

660
00:41:43,797 --> 00:41:45,840
You know what that means, Mr. Krabs.

661
00:41:46,425 --> 00:41:48,969
I'm in deep shrimp.

662
00:41:49,052 --> 00:41:51,387
SpongeBob!

663
00:41:51,471 --> 00:41:55,224
Hold on, lad!

664
00:41:58,353 --> 00:42:00,063
Whoo-hoo!

665
00:42:00,147 --> 00:42:03,024
Onto challenge number two!

666
00:42:06,278 --> 00:42:09,114
Shello?

667
00:42:09,197 --> 00:42:11,616
Bad news, sir. Krabs is following us.

668
00:42:11,700 --> 00:42:14,536
What? No, no, no!

669
00:42:14,619 --> 00:42:18,789
If he catches up, he'll tell SpongeBob
the truth and ruin everything.

670
00:42:18,874 --> 00:42:20,208
Oh, Barb,

671
00:42:20,292 --> 00:42:24,212
it's been so long and I'm so close.

672
00:42:24,296 --> 00:42:26,131
I wouldn't worry about Krabs, sir.

673
00:42:27,716 --> 00:42:31,803
He ain't gonna last long
in the Underworld.

674
00:42:39,561 --> 00:42:42,939
Huh? Where is that music comin' from?

675
00:42:43,648 --> 00:42:45,358
Mmm. Not bad.

676
00:42:46,026 --> 00:42:47,068
Huh?

677
00:43:00,082 --> 00:43:01,124
Huh?

678
00:43:07,589 --> 00:43:09,424
Greetings, travelers.

679
00:43:09,508 --> 00:43:11,676
Come play with us.

680
00:43:12,552 --> 00:43:14,053
Come play?

681
00:43:14,137 --> 00:43:15,763
Cover your ears, Squidward.

682
00:43:15,847 --> 00:43:19,934
Those are Sirens, temptin' us
into a smooth jazz trap.

683
00:43:21,186 --> 00:43:22,812
Later, losers.

684
00:43:26,024 --> 00:43:28,359
Squidward. We got to save SpongeBob.

685
00:43:31,780 --> 00:43:34,115
There's no time for a solo!

686
00:43:34,199 --> 00:43:36,826
There's always time for a solo.

687
00:43:43,667 --> 00:43:44,668
Meow.

688
00:43:52,634 --> 00:43:56,012
Well, music lovers,
what do you think? Ack!

689
00:43:56,096 --> 00:43:57,806
Help me!

690
00:43:57,889 --> 00:43:59,807
Ooh, now we got to save that

691
00:43:59,891 --> 00:44:01,809
good-for-nothin'
easy-listenin' layabout.

692
00:44:01,893 --> 00:44:03,269
Help me!

693
00:44:04,855 --> 00:44:06,731
Whoa! Put me down!

694
00:44:09,234 --> 00:44:11,569
There's got to be somethin' in here
that'll help Squidward.

695
00:44:11,653 --> 00:44:12,654
Hmm.

696
00:44:13,113 --> 00:44:14,364
Whoa!

697
00:44:15,907 --> 00:44:17,617
- Huh?
- Better hurry up!

698
00:44:17,701 --> 00:44:20,328
Or instead of being a big guy,
I'll be a dead guy.

699
00:44:24,541 --> 00:44:25,542
Whoa!

700
00:44:25,625 --> 00:44:27,877
Bandages, no. Antiseptic, no.

701
00:44:27,961 --> 00:44:29,921
Flare gun, no. Breath mints, no.

702
00:44:30,005 --> 00:44:31,297
Huh? Whoa-hoo! Agh!

703
00:44:32,090 --> 00:44:33,299
Help!

704
00:44:33,592 --> 00:44:35,677
- Squawk!
- Oh, no, you don't!

705
00:44:47,606 --> 00:44:48,607
Uh-oh.

706
00:44:53,195 --> 00:44:54,696
No more wastin' time, Squidward.

707
00:44:55,322 --> 00:44:58,116
We might already be too late!

708
00:45:06,249 --> 00:45:09,085
You know, I think we cracked the code
to these challenges.

709
00:45:09,169 --> 00:45:11,796
All I got to do is keep acting
like Mr. Krabs,

710
00:45:11,880 --> 00:45:14,173
and I'll be swashbuckling in no time.

711
00:45:14,257 --> 00:45:16,092
To Mr. Krabs.

712
00:45:16,176 --> 00:45:17,468
- Big guys!
- Big guys!

713
00:45:22,682 --> 00:45:24,934
Oh, what are they doin' now?

714
00:45:25,018 --> 00:45:27,937
Uh, eh... You can
celebrate later, lad!

715
00:45:28,021 --> 00:45:30,898
Let's head to the next challenge!

716
00:45:32,943 --> 00:45:34,194
SpongeBob?

717
00:45:35,862 --> 00:45:36,863
Whee!

718
00:45:36,947 --> 00:45:40,742
His pink friend
is slowing us down.

719
00:45:40,825 --> 00:45:43,327
Oh, just give me five minutes
with him, sir.

720
00:45:43,411 --> 00:45:47,748
I'll explain
how we do things around here!

721
00:45:49,125 --> 00:45:51,335
Okay, chill out, Barb.

722
00:45:51,419 --> 00:45:54,004
I have a better idea.

723
00:45:56,341 --> 00:45:57,759
SpongeBob.

724
00:45:57,842 --> 00:46:01,303
Swashbucklers don't spend their time
seahorsin' around.

725
00:46:01,388 --> 00:46:02,597
Really?

726
00:46:02,681 --> 00:46:04,974
What's the swashbuckling stance
on giggling?

727
00:46:06,142 --> 00:46:07,935
Not good!

728
00:46:08,019 --> 00:46:10,980
What about butt wiggling?

729
00:46:12,857 --> 00:46:16,360
Maybe you don't want this
bad enough, SpongeBob.

730
00:46:16,444 --> 00:46:17,611
That's not true.

731
00:46:17,696 --> 00:46:19,781
I want to be a big guy
more than anything.

732
00:46:19,864 --> 00:46:23,450
Well, uh, if you want
to be someone big,

733
00:46:23,535 --> 00:46:28,035
you're gonna have to leave
some of your small ways behind. Hmm?

734
00:46:37,299 --> 00:46:39,884
Oh. Hmm.

735
00:46:40,468 --> 00:46:43,095
Okay. No more seahorsing around.

736
00:46:43,179 --> 00:46:44,763
Smart lad!

737
00:46:44,848 --> 00:46:48,643
Now, let's get you
to challenge number two!

738
00:46:51,896 --> 00:46:53,272
Ow!

739
00:46:53,356 --> 00:46:55,983
<i>Welcome to the Underworld</i>

740
00:46:56,067 --> 00:46:59,528
for what promises
to be an exciting contest.

741
00:46:59,612 --> 00:47:04,033
We're just moments away
from challenge number two.

742
00:47:04,117 --> 00:47:06,035
Tell me, Barb,

743
00:47:06,119 --> 00:47:10,164
will it be even more difficult
than the last challenge?

744
00:47:10,248 --> 00:47:12,041
Uh, yes.

745
00:47:12,125 --> 00:47:15,044
<i>There's, uh, no telling
what's lurking along</i>

746
00:47:15,128 --> 00:47:16,754
<i>that path to the platform.</i>

747
00:47:16,838 --> 00:47:19,382
<i>It could be a charging Bull Clam.</i>

748
00:47:19,466 --> 00:47:21,468
<i>Or a terrifying JellyHook.</i>

749
00:47:21,551 --> 00:47:23,761
<i>Hope it's not my
third-grade math teacher.</i>

750
00:47:23,845 --> 00:47:26,848
She scares the heck out of me!

751
00:47:26,931 --> 00:47:29,099
- Know what I'm saying?
- You're on my foot.

752
00:47:29,184 --> 00:47:31,477
Let's meet our challenger!

753
00:47:32,062 --> 00:47:34,355
<i>Standing at a full 36 clams high</i>

754
00:47:34,439 --> 00:47:37,483
<i>and hailing all the way
from Bikini Bottom,</i>

755
00:47:37,567 --> 00:47:39,235
<i>my best friend,</i>

756
00:47:39,319 --> 00:47:42,864
<i>SpongeBerb SquareShorts.</i>

757
00:47:42,947 --> 00:47:45,491
<i>This bubble blower
has got a lot to prove</i>

758
00:47:45,575 --> 00:47:48,869
<i>if he ever wants to show the world
he's a swashbuckler.</i>

759
00:47:51,081 --> 00:47:54,125
Challenge number two won't be easy.

760
00:47:54,209 --> 00:47:57,921
But I believe in you, big guy.

761
00:47:58,004 --> 00:48:00,339
Now, go get 'em.

762
00:48:00,423 --> 00:48:01,424
Big guy.

763
00:48:01,508 --> 00:48:04,427
Big guy. Big guy. Big guy. Big guy.
Big guy. Big guy. Big guy.

764
00:48:07,430 --> 00:48:08,431
Yikes!

765
00:48:16,147 --> 00:48:17,648
Yeow!

766
00:48:23,321 --> 00:48:25,698
Okay, SquarePants, you can do this.

767
00:48:26,825 --> 00:48:28,785
<i>What would I do?</i>

768
00:48:28,868 --> 00:48:29,869
Hmm.

769
00:48:31,037 --> 00:48:32,329
- Huh?
- Huh?

770
00:48:34,082 --> 00:48:37,543
Whoa!

771
00:48:37,627 --> 00:48:39,086
Whee!

772
00:48:40,255 --> 00:48:42,131
Whoo-hoo!

773
00:48:42,215 --> 00:48:44,550
Oh, my God! Yeah!

774
00:48:44,634 --> 00:48:46,135
Yeah, baby!

775
00:48:47,929 --> 00:48:49,055
Whoo-hoo!

776
00:48:53,017 --> 00:48:54,101
Whoo-hoo!

777
00:49:01,776 --> 00:49:03,402
Ooh, your lucky brick.

778
00:49:09,033 --> 00:49:10,117
- Huh?
- Ooh!

779
00:49:10,201 --> 00:49:11,202
Huh?

780
00:49:15,123 --> 00:49:16,207
Whoo!

781
00:49:20,670 --> 00:49:21,754
Hmm.

782
00:49:24,591 --> 00:49:25,967
Whee!

783
00:49:26,426 --> 00:49:27,427
Huh?

784
00:49:39,856 --> 00:49:41,232
<i>En garde!</i>

785
00:49:58,541 --> 00:49:59,959
Huh-ho!

786
00:50:00,043 --> 00:50:01,252
Hyah!

787
00:50:03,588 --> 00:50:06,048
Whoo-hoo! Yeah!

788
00:50:23,608 --> 00:50:24,817
<i>We interrupt this movie</i>

789
00:50:24,901 --> 00:50:26,944
<i>for an important message
from Paramount Studios.</i>

790
00:50:27,028 --> 00:50:30,614
This picture's gone completely
off the rails!

791
00:50:30,698 --> 00:50:34,702
The only thing that can save it
is some serious star power.

792
00:50:34,786 --> 00:50:38,581
Get Sandy Cheeks
in this movie, pronto!

793
00:50:38,665 --> 00:50:40,458
Howdy-do, SpongeBob!

794
00:50:40,542 --> 00:50:41,751
Huh.

795
00:50:43,378 --> 00:50:45,421
That's not what I meant!

796
00:50:45,505 --> 00:50:47,215
Who is it?

797
00:50:47,632 --> 00:50:49,508
Hey, what--

798
00:50:49,592 --> 00:50:51,260
Get out of here! Get out!

799
00:51:10,029 --> 00:51:11,030
Huh?

800
00:51:27,130 --> 00:51:28,881
- Whoo-hoo!
- Yeah!

801
00:51:28,965 --> 00:51:31,926
Boy, if only Mr. Krabs
could see me now.

802
00:51:32,010 --> 00:51:36,055
He'd finally see
what I've been seein' all along,

803
00:51:36,139 --> 00:51:38,099
a swashbuckler in the makin'.

804
00:51:38,182 --> 00:51:40,726
- Really?
- Really.

805
00:51:40,810 --> 00:51:44,355
But remember,
if you want to become a true big guy,

806
00:51:44,439 --> 00:51:46,691
you have to stay focused.

807
00:51:46,774 --> 00:51:48,317
Got it. Focused.

808
00:51:48,401 --> 00:51:49,610
Bubble break!

809
00:51:51,946 --> 00:51:53,864
You had me at "bubble."

810
00:51:56,659 --> 00:51:59,828
Let's do a triple-dog
backslash wand-grabber.

811
00:51:59,912 --> 00:52:03,081
With a banana-slap twist-blister!

812
00:52:06,836 --> 00:52:07,837
Hmm?

813
00:52:08,963 --> 00:52:11,215
- Huh?
- Yeah, um...

814
00:52:12,133 --> 00:52:13,884
sounds fun, Patrick,

815
00:52:13,968 --> 00:52:16,428
but maybe we shouldn't
do this anymore.

816
00:52:16,512 --> 00:52:17,638
What?

817
00:52:17,722 --> 00:52:20,516
Well, it's just-- You know, it--

818
00:52:20,600 --> 00:52:22,643
I have this other thing I'm doing.

819
00:52:22,727 --> 00:52:26,272
You mean,
you don't want to blow bubbles

820
00:52:26,356 --> 00:52:27,648
with me?

821
00:52:33,363 --> 00:52:34,989
I really want to, but...

822
00:52:35,490 --> 00:52:37,783
- That's okay.
- It's just that I should...

823
00:52:37,867 --> 00:52:39,535
No, it's fine.

824
00:52:39,619 --> 00:52:42,121
- Pat.
- I'm not crying!

825
00:52:42,205 --> 00:52:44,498
It's just raining on my face!

826
00:52:45,667 --> 00:52:48,294
Ah, don't worry about your friend.

827
00:52:48,378 --> 00:52:51,923
You can make it up to him
once you're a swashbuckler.

828
00:52:52,006 --> 00:52:53,507
Well, I guess.

829
00:52:53,591 --> 00:52:57,720
Good lad.
Just keep your eyes on the prize.

830
00:53:00,098 --> 00:53:02,558
Come on. Almost there.

831
00:53:02,642 --> 00:53:05,436
You're pushing this tub way too hard.

832
00:53:05,520 --> 00:53:08,064
We can't stop
until we reach SpongeBob!

833
00:53:08,147 --> 00:53:10,190
Can't stop. Won't stop.

834
00:53:10,274 --> 00:53:11,733
No stop!

835
00:53:18,324 --> 00:53:19,408
We stopped.

836
00:53:20,618 --> 00:53:23,495
Oh, I'm so sorry, me boy.

837
00:53:23,579 --> 00:53:28,079
Why didn't I just show ya how to be
a swashbuckler when ya asked?

838
00:53:29,419 --> 00:53:31,879
You never told me how much you cared.

839
00:53:31,963 --> 00:53:36,463
Well, I couldn't. Emotions that
are emotional are hard for me!

840
00:53:37,176 --> 00:53:39,178
Well, it doesn't matter now.

841
00:53:39,262 --> 00:53:43,099
- What?
- You're stuck, so I'm doomed.

842
00:53:43,641 --> 00:53:46,477
Goodbye!

843
00:53:46,561 --> 00:53:49,230
Quick! We got to fix this camper!
We got to fix it!

844
00:53:49,313 --> 00:53:50,689
Oh, sure.

845
00:53:50,773 --> 00:53:55,273
Let's go pop into an
auto parts store and get what we need.

846
00:53:55,403 --> 00:53:56,404
- Meow.
- Huh?

847
00:53:58,656 --> 00:53:59,865
Good eye, Gary!

848
00:53:59,949 --> 00:54:02,159
Does this seem a little convenient?

849
00:54:02,243 --> 00:54:03,327
Nonsense.

850
00:54:03,411 --> 00:54:06,163
These big-box stores are everywhere!

851
00:54:09,417 --> 00:54:10,418
Meow.

852
00:54:10,501 --> 00:54:12,419
Spare tire, exhaust pipe,

853
00:54:12,503 --> 00:54:14,880
tire iron, and oil.

854
00:54:14,964 --> 00:54:17,007
Oil, oil, where's the oil?

855
00:54:17,091 --> 00:54:18,842
Just ask somebody.

856
00:54:19,969 --> 00:54:22,346
Hello! We need some oil over here!

857
00:54:23,765 --> 00:54:24,932
Hello?

858
00:54:25,725 --> 00:54:27,435
Hello!

859
00:54:28,019 --> 00:54:29,395
Where is everybody?

860
00:54:31,606 --> 00:54:34,650
- Hello?
- That might be our cue to go.

861
00:54:35,109 --> 00:54:37,402
- Meow-ow.
- Huh. There's someone's shoe.

862
00:54:38,696 --> 00:54:40,197
And there's the other one.

863
00:54:50,708 --> 00:54:53,752
What kind of big-box store is this?

864
00:54:56,964 --> 00:54:59,007
Run!

865
00:55:03,513 --> 00:55:06,015
I see the exit!

866
00:55:25,827 --> 00:55:26,828
Meow-ow.

867
00:55:31,749 --> 00:55:34,084
What's the plan, Mr. Krabs?

868
00:55:34,168 --> 00:55:35,210
Meow.

869
00:55:35,294 --> 00:55:36,295
Meow-ow.

870
00:55:36,379 --> 00:55:39,048
It looks hungry.
And it's getting closer!

871
00:55:39,131 --> 00:55:40,132
Meow.

872
00:55:41,551 --> 00:55:43,010
Say the word.

873
00:55:43,094 --> 00:55:44,762
Anytime now.

874
00:55:44,846 --> 00:55:45,972
Sooner the better!

875
00:55:50,935 --> 00:55:51,936
Really?

876
00:55:52,019 --> 00:55:53,020
Meow.

877
00:56:05,199 --> 00:56:06,200
Huh?

878
00:56:07,118 --> 00:56:08,577
Hey, I found the oil!

879
00:56:09,161 --> 00:56:10,162
Oh, no, no, no, no!

880
00:56:13,457 --> 00:56:15,959
Bye-bye, Krabby.

881
00:56:18,504 --> 00:56:20,380
Huh?

882
00:56:20,923 --> 00:56:21,924
Whoa...

883
00:56:23,843 --> 00:56:25,553
Barb?

884
00:56:25,636 --> 00:56:30,136
What do you do when your best friend
doesn't want to blow bubbles anymore?

885
00:56:31,767 --> 00:56:32,768
Uh...

886
00:56:33,102 --> 00:56:34,353
Well, I, uh...

887
00:56:34,437 --> 00:56:38,937
- Yeah, I, uh...
- Thanks. Makes a lot of sense.

888
00:56:47,658 --> 00:56:51,078
This is it, lad.
The last challenge.

889
00:56:51,162 --> 00:56:55,662
Finish this
and you'll become a swashbuckler!

890
00:56:58,002 --> 00:56:59,294
Let's do it.

891
00:57:12,183 --> 00:57:13,642
Ready, Dutch?

892
00:57:14,352 --> 00:57:16,354
Bang it.

893
00:57:31,869 --> 00:57:32,870
Ta-da!

894
00:57:32,954 --> 00:57:34,372
Daring, bravery,
courageousness,

895
00:57:34,455 --> 00:57:35,998
panache, guts, grit, moxie...

896
00:57:36,082 --> 00:57:38,209
...and intestinal fortitude!

897
00:57:38,292 --> 00:57:42,379
You did 'em all!
I knew you were special, lad.

898
00:57:59,146 --> 00:58:02,149
Whoa!

899
00:58:02,233 --> 00:58:03,943
Look at that!

900
00:58:04,026 --> 00:58:08,071
Inside those doors,
you'll stand at the altar,

901
00:58:08,155 --> 00:58:09,614
blow the hornpipe,

902
00:58:09,699 --> 00:58:12,034
and a swashbuckler you'll become.

903
00:58:12,118 --> 00:58:14,203
And once I get my certificate,

904
00:58:14,286 --> 00:58:18,164
Mr. Krabs will finally see
that I'm a big guy.

905
00:58:19,333 --> 00:58:23,754
Then I can do what every little guy
dreams of doing when he grows up,

906
00:58:23,838 --> 00:58:26,465
ride that big guy roller coaster.

907
00:58:26,549 --> 00:58:29,343
Yes, roller coa-- Uh, wait.

908
00:58:29,427 --> 00:58:32,805
You mean your dream is
to ride a roller coaster?

909
00:58:32,888 --> 00:58:35,599
Well, of course. We all have dreams.

910
00:58:35,683 --> 00:58:36,684
What's yours?

911
00:58:36,767 --> 00:58:37,768
What?

912
00:58:38,686 --> 00:58:39,895
Well, uh...

913
00:58:39,979 --> 00:58:43,774
I dream of a wonderful world
above the waves,

914
00:58:43,858 --> 00:58:48,358
where the sun shines in your face
and the wind blows through your hair.

915
00:58:49,030 --> 00:58:51,240
What's this magical place called?

916
00:58:51,824 --> 00:58:53,826
Santa Monica!

917
00:58:53,909 --> 00:58:57,495
Look at me,
chatterin' like a cabin boy.

918
00:58:58,956 --> 00:59:00,540
- Let's get goin'!
- Stop right there!

919
00:59:04,295 --> 00:59:06,964
Good thing this bird is allergic
to shellfish!

920
00:59:09,383 --> 00:59:11,093
Mr. Krabs?

921
00:59:11,177 --> 00:59:12,845
Ooh! Tartar sauce!

922
00:59:16,098 --> 00:59:17,390
Are you okay, boy-o?

923
00:59:17,475 --> 00:59:20,603
Did ya get hurt at all?
Any bumps? Bruises? Scratches?

924
00:59:20,686 --> 00:59:23,146
I'm so glad we found you!

925
00:59:23,230 --> 00:59:25,774
- Who's "we"?
- Me, Squidward and Gary.

926
00:59:31,781 --> 00:59:34,575
We're here to rescue ya! From him!

927
00:59:34,658 --> 00:59:36,993
Whoa! Well, now hold on, Krabs!

928
00:59:37,078 --> 00:59:38,454
Oh, I'm not in any danger.

929
00:59:38,537 --> 00:59:41,248
The Flying Dutchman's been helping me
become a swashbuckler.

930
00:59:41,332 --> 00:59:43,083
- Just like you.
- Oh.

931
00:59:44,960 --> 00:59:46,962
Well, ya see, I, uh...

932
00:59:47,046 --> 00:59:49,798
You want to tell him, or should I?

933
00:59:49,882 --> 00:59:50,883
Tell me what?

934
00:59:52,635 --> 00:59:56,388
It's about me past, lad.
I embellished a few o' the...

935
00:59:56,472 --> 00:59:58,765
tsk, uh, finer details.

936
01:00:01,268 --> 01:00:05,768
<i>I did spend me youth at sea,
but I wasn't the captain.</i>

937
01:00:07,483 --> 01:00:09,818
<i>Wait a minute.
You were a fry cook?</i>

938
01:00:09,902 --> 01:00:14,402
<i>Aye. And like you,
I dreamed of bein' a swashbuckler.</i>

939
01:00:20,371 --> 01:00:24,375
<i>But nobody believed in me.
They said I was a--</i>

940
01:00:24,458 --> 01:00:27,043
<i>Bubble-blowin' baby boy!</i>

941
01:00:27,128 --> 01:00:29,130
<i>I was so ashamed.</i>

942
01:00:30,381 --> 01:00:33,717
<i>And that's when something
called out to me.</i>

943
01:00:35,803 --> 01:00:38,388
<i>It was the Dutchman's hornpipe.</i>

944
01:00:39,932 --> 01:00:41,016
Huh?

945
01:00:43,352 --> 01:00:47,564
<i>The dirty deceiver promised
to make me a swashbuckler,</i>

946
01:00:47,648 --> 01:00:50,317
<i>and lured me to the Underworld.</i>

947
01:00:50,401 --> 01:00:54,238
<i>But I froze when I saw
that terrifyin' place.</i>

948
01:00:56,574 --> 01:01:01,074
<i>The Underworld shivered me timbers
and I ran home, tail between me legs.</i>

949
01:01:02,163 --> 01:01:04,832
I had many adventures at sea, boy,

950
01:01:04,915 --> 01:01:08,209
but I never did become a swashbuckler.

951
01:01:08,294 --> 01:01:11,422
But, what about
the Swashbuckler Certificate?

952
01:01:11,505 --> 01:01:14,049
Well, about that...

953
01:01:19,388 --> 01:01:23,433
I've been battling
the horrors of the Underworld

954
01:01:23,517 --> 01:01:25,644
for a Kids' Menu?

955
01:01:25,728 --> 01:01:27,980
I thought it looked familiar.

956
01:01:28,063 --> 01:01:30,398
I'm sorry I lied, lad.

957
01:01:30,482 --> 01:01:33,818
I just couldn't bear
for you to know I was a coward.

958
01:01:33,903 --> 01:01:37,865
But I'm tellin' you the truth now.
The Dutchman is trickin' ya!

959
01:01:37,948 --> 01:01:41,368
No, he's not. He's just helping me
become a swashbuckler.

960
01:01:41,452 --> 01:01:43,162
I thought you'd be proud of me.

961
01:01:43,662 --> 01:01:47,457
Instead, you're treating me
like I'm still just a bubble blower.

962
01:01:47,541 --> 01:01:51,211
That's right.
Krabs has never believed in you.

963
01:01:51,295 --> 01:01:54,131
Come with me and blow that hornpipe.

964
01:01:54,215 --> 01:01:57,134
Show him you're a real swashbuckler.

965
01:01:57,218 --> 01:01:59,929
The biggest of the big guys.

966
01:02:01,889 --> 01:02:03,265
I'm ready.

967
01:02:04,725 --> 01:02:05,809
No, SpongeBob!

968
01:02:07,102 --> 01:02:08,353
Wait!

969
01:02:10,731 --> 01:02:13,066
Hurry, lad. On the pedestal.

970
01:02:15,694 --> 01:02:18,029
SpongeBob! Don't do it!

971
01:02:18,113 --> 01:02:21,866
You'll see, Mr. Krabs.
I'm gonna be a big guy.

972
01:02:21,951 --> 01:02:23,702
No! No, no, no!

973
01:02:25,329 --> 01:02:26,621
Come on now!

974
01:02:27,998 --> 01:02:29,708
Hurry.

975
01:02:29,792 --> 01:02:31,210
SpongeBob!

976
01:02:31,293 --> 01:02:32,544
Meow, meow, meow, meow!

977
01:02:49,478 --> 01:02:52,731
- No!
- Too late, Krabby!

978
01:02:55,067 --> 01:02:57,152
I'll save ya, lad!

979
01:02:58,237 --> 01:02:59,238
Gotcha!

980
01:02:59,321 --> 01:03:01,114
No, no, no, no, no!

981
01:03:01,198 --> 01:03:03,783
Whoa!

982
01:03:07,788 --> 01:03:08,830
Ooh!

983
01:03:08,914 --> 01:03:10,624
Swashbuckler shine!

984
01:03:10,708 --> 01:03:13,544
It's not swashbuckler shine.

985
01:03:13,627 --> 01:03:16,338
Yeah, no. It ain't.

986
01:03:16,422 --> 01:03:18,132
Huh?

987
01:03:41,071 --> 01:03:42,447
No!

988
01:03:45,701 --> 01:03:47,661
Squawk.

989
01:03:47,745 --> 01:03:51,874
My curse is lifted!

990
01:03:51,957 --> 01:03:54,834
- What?
- I tricked you.

991
01:03:54,918 --> 01:03:59,418
Oh, you're such a big guy,
ready to be a swashbuckler!

992
01:04:02,009 --> 01:04:06,509
It's all been a big lie,
and you fell for it.

993
01:04:07,431 --> 01:04:08,807
Huh?

994
01:04:08,891 --> 01:04:10,684
Oh, no.

995
01:04:18,275 --> 01:04:21,152
Hang on to your square derriere.

996
01:04:22,613 --> 01:04:25,490
Guess who's cursed now?

997
01:04:25,574 --> 01:04:26,575
Meow.

998
01:04:29,411 --> 01:04:33,911
All hail the new FlyingBob DutchPants!

999
01:04:35,459 --> 01:04:37,544
What?

1000
01:04:37,628 --> 01:04:41,340
Oh, Mr. Krabs,
you were right about him.

1001
01:04:41,799 --> 01:04:44,301
Mr. Krabs!

1002
01:04:44,385 --> 01:04:45,594
Ugh!

1003
01:04:45,677 --> 01:04:48,721
It looks like you got
a little Dutchman on you, too.

1004
01:04:50,516 --> 01:04:52,726
It's a double Dutchman, sir.

1005
01:04:55,229 --> 01:04:56,563
You tricked me.

1006
01:04:56,647 --> 01:05:01,147
Well, you wanted to be
a big guy swashbuckler, didn't you?

1007
01:05:01,777 --> 01:05:03,695
So what are you complainin' about?

1008
01:05:03,779 --> 01:05:06,364
You should be thankin' me.

1009
01:05:07,533 --> 01:05:11,036
No. Please, Mr. Dutchman, sir.
I changed my mind.

1010
01:05:11,120 --> 01:05:13,747
I don't want to be
a swashbuckler anymore.

1011
01:05:13,831 --> 01:05:16,291
Oh, don't fret, sailor.

1012
01:05:16,834 --> 01:05:18,168
All you need to do

1013
01:05:18,252 --> 01:05:22,089
is find someone to trick
into trading places with you.

1014
01:05:22,172 --> 01:05:23,590
It only took me...

1015
01:05:24,299 --> 01:05:26,342
Let's see, uh...

1016
01:05:26,427 --> 01:05:28,303
500 years!

1017
01:05:29,596 --> 01:05:31,264
Oh!

1018
01:05:34,143 --> 01:05:37,479
Now I finally get to go home.

1019
01:05:37,563 --> 01:05:39,481
Yep, we got to run.

1020
01:05:39,565 --> 01:05:40,566
Huh?

1021
01:05:40,649 --> 01:05:42,233
Whoa!

1022
01:05:42,317 --> 01:05:44,736
Wait. Aren't you taking me?

1023
01:05:44,820 --> 01:05:48,365
Why would I do that?
I don't need you anymore.

1024
01:06:13,056 --> 01:06:15,099
What have I done?

1025
01:06:16,477 --> 01:06:18,437
It's not your fault, lad.

1026
01:06:18,520 --> 01:06:21,397
It was my lyin' that led ya here.

1027
01:06:21,482 --> 01:06:25,444
And now we're cursed
to be ghosts forever.

1028
01:06:27,321 --> 01:06:29,114
Forever?

1029
01:06:29,198 --> 01:06:30,657
Forever.

1030
01:06:31,450 --> 01:06:32,993
Forever, forever?

1031
01:06:33,785 --> 01:06:35,536
Forever, forever.

1032
01:06:37,831 --> 01:06:40,792
Forever, forever, forever, forever,
forever, forever, forever, forever?

1033
01:06:40,876 --> 01:06:43,295
Forever, forever, forever, forever,
forever, forever.

1034
01:06:43,378 --> 01:06:44,379
Forever.

1035
01:06:45,130 --> 01:06:46,840
- One more.
- Forever!

1036
01:06:49,843 --> 01:06:53,721
